  "prompt": "How does counselling for andhra pradesh students work?",
  "response": "Counselling for Andhra Pradesh students typically works as follows:\n\n1. For Professional Courses:\n- APSCHE (Andhra Pradesh State Council of Higher Education) coordinates counselling\n- Online registration process\n- Candidates fill choices based on their entrance exam ranks\n- Seat allocation through a centralized counselling system\n- Multiple rounds of counselling conducted\n- Options for engineering, medical, pharmacy, and other professional courses\n\n2. Engineering Counselling:\n- Based on EAMCET/APEAMCET rank\n- Online registration on official website\n- Choice filling and locking\n- Seat allocation based on rank and preferences\n- Physical verification of documents\n\n3. Medical Counselling:\n- Based on NEET rank\n- Separate counselling for government and private colleges\n- Online registration process\n- Seat allocation according to rank and category\n\n4. Key Steps:\n- Register online\n- Pay counselling fee\n- Submit required documents\n- Fill course and college preferences\n- Participate in seat allocation rounds\n- Complete admission process after seat allotment\n\n5. Important Platforms:\n- Official APSCHE website\n- Individual college websites\n- Online counselling portals\n\nThe specific process can vary slightly depending on the course and current year's guidelines.",
